      <title>Top 10 - beta</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=monkbalance&amp;message.id=10425#M10425</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;OK guys n gals, I’ve put a fair amount of time into this so far, I hope it’s the right “direction” in format and content. At the moment, it’s a draft so there is probably some spelling mistakes, I’m sure many grammatical mistakes, but hopefully the content should be mostly ok.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Also note that the “ordering” is not of any importance. I’ve therefore left them in the same order as before with “empty” slots. We could in theory re-order them so the empty slots are at the bottom, but until we decide what to do with those slots I’ll leave the ordering as it is.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The new “format” for each item in the top 10 is as follows;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;N. A title&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The “primary” item of the topic - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;The current SOE status&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;A [ long ] explanation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;A bullet list of issues &amp;amp; fixes to do with this topic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additional ideas based on this topic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The explanation is a re-wording of what’s already there along with extracts from various sources (i.e. MB etc) and a good chunk of what I perceive the issue to be.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Now I’m sure some of you won’t agree on the full content of the explanation, but I’ve had to keep it so it’s reasonably concise, and captures the feeling of the majority of the community without leaving anything important out. It’s not supposed to be a full blown discussion on the topic, just something that a developer can use as a “quick overview”. Remember, the whole purpose of this is for SoE developers, to let them know what our issues are, to let them know how we'd like them to be fixed or addressed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;p align="center"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;Monks Top 10 List (beta 11 Feb 2006)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;1. Riposte “Immunity”&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Some form of riposte immunity - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;No development feedback at this time&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Monks in a DPS role are generally hitting mobs from behind, however there are times when we are hitting from in front, either by design (mob positioning via Dragon Punch or balancing raid push) or by accident (mob spin). Mobs can do a huge amount of damage on a riposte (1500+ per riposte is common nowadays on trash, and boss mobs riposte for 4k+) This is a lot of “subsidiary” damage we are taking as a DPS class that others whose role is also a DPS class are not as often exposed to (i.e. all DPS casters).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Monks get a lot of strikethrough (via items, and 2 AA lines – Strikethrough and Style of the Mimic), however the mob still gets “an attack” when you “strike through” a riposte, and if it hits you still take damage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Back when mobs only hit for 300 or 400 max, a riposte was of little consequence. Now it’s often the case a double riposte for 4k each can kill a monk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Given SoE’s oft stated, “damage from any angle” role for monks, it’s currently the case that this is not possible because attacking from the front can result in taking serious damage or even death, and an unwarranted load on healers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An AA line to give a chance of immunity to ripostes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An AA line to tie in Strikethrough to riposte immunity so that if you strike through an opponents attack, you do NOT take riposte damage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These AAs would only work when NOT top of the agro list&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These AA’s would not work against ENRAGE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fix strikethrough so that you do not get riposted when you strikethrough a riposte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt; 2. Monk Relative DPS vs other pure melee and other DPS classes&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Actually get an update on the class re-balancing of DPS (“round 2”) - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;DPS evaluation for all classes has begun and will be the focus of part #2 of the class Re-Envision process&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Monks being one of the three pure DPS classes, [ we feel ] are slightly unbalanced in our relative DPS given like-for-like AA/itemisation against the other melee and “DPS” classes, and the inherent risks we take as a melee class (ie, AoE rampage, ripostes, mobs moving/OOR etc).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’d like to see the results of the DPS re-evaluation “round 2” mentioned many times, and as part of this;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Further evaluation of current monk special attacks&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A new “special” kick style attack&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;3. Itemisation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weight of items - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently the biggest issue monks have with itemisation is the weight of items. Many items are far too heavy for monks, even some monk specific items. For example, a full set of DoN cultural with a few bags and average weapons will put a monk overweight. GM symbol augments that weigh 0.5 each again, over 8 slots is far too much. At most they should be 0.1 weight, or even 0 like 90% of all other augments. When items are introduced, we feel it’s very important that when the item is melee orientated it’s weight is carefully considered with the monk weight limit in mind. Items that are “leather class” based again should be considered carefully with monks weight limit in mind, as Druids and Beastlords do not have the same weight limitation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Over expansions we’ve found this is often “forgotten”, with each expansion item weights getting higher and higher, and often each expansion items having to be lowered in weight for the monks via a patch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Continuation of the “pouches” introduced with DoDH in future expansions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Careful consideration of the focus effects on future sets of monk armour. The current Anguish items with high Strikethough and zero accuracy is seen by many as asinine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;A further line of player made throwing items (cf. Javelins), ie, shurikens.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;More “robe” BP graphics for those who wish to see robes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;More “leather” graphics for those who wish to see the “leather” look - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;4. EMPTY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This item is currently empty (was innate run speed).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;5. Mend Skill&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An AA to reduce the refresh timer on MEND - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mend has been in the game, unchanged since day one except for the critical mend line that came in when AA’s were first introduced. Whilst a 25% base (50% crit via AA) mend is useful, in today’s game with trash mobs that hit for over 10% of your HP’s PER HIT, we feel it’s time the mend skill got a little additional help beyond the current “critical mend” AA we have.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Add a new AA: Hastened Mend&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;N levels, X percent reduction in timer per level (ie, 5 levels, 6 % per level, down to 4:12 mins )&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Have the tickdown timer on MEND showing how long to refresh once used like other hot keys (ie, Dragon Fang).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;6. EMPTY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This item is currently empty (was Leather graphics, now integrated into item 3)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;7. Disc stacking&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Earthwalk (&amp;amp; Stonestance) should be on it’s own timer (not on the Voiddance/Whirlwind timer) - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Several of the monk disciplines are on the same timer, and in some cases this is overly detrimental, especially when discs now cost END to use so cannot be chained. Using Voiddance (a level 54 disc) currently disables Earthwalk (a 65 disc) for 40 minutes !.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Throw Stone should be on different timer than Lulls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dragon Fang should be on a different timer than Lulls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;8. Weight Limit&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An actual benefit for being under weight - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently there is no benefit for being “under weight”, only a penalty for being over weight (that being a scaling decrease in the avoidance part of AC as weight goes up.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The whole concept of a “weight limit” has long been unexplained by SoE given the modern game and modern itemisation, and especially with recent expansions with even some earrings weighing over 1 each, this is often not a limitation, but rather a huge burden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additionally, the weight limit a long time ago was made to scale with level, starting at a base 14, topping out at &amp;lt; 25 at level 60. However, this cap has not changed with the level 65, and level 70 increases as it should in theory have.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Increase the weight limit cap for level 65 and level 70&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additional Innate increase to runspeed for being underweight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Innate increase in avoidance for bring underweight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Innate increase in attack speed for being underweight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;9. Avoidance&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;An increase to avoidance - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently waiting on the outcome of Masters Aura (PoR disc, +5% block/parry/riposte) to see how this affects “avoidance” (via the increase to block and riposte) before expanding on this topic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;10. EMPTY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This item is currently empty (was ranged item)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Items that could replace the “empty” slots as follows. I’ve not fully fleshed these out yet as I just wanted to give an idea of some different topic headers that could go in there;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;A. Monk Lull&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Increase the level of mobs that lull affects&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The monk “lull” discs were added with the GoD expansion to give monks more of an even level against other pulling classes. The lulls have scaled up to the OoW expansion so that they cap out at level 70. However with DoDH, many mobs in even mid-difficulty instances are over the level 70 cap, or are totally immune to lull.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Change refresh time on lulls so that more than 1 mob can be lulled&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B. Pulling Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content that needs pulling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;One of the primary functions of a monk is pulling. In the OoW expansion this lessened somewhat with open zones, and in DoN disappeared altogether with almost no pulling required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;With DoDH, the pulling role has been somewhat re-established, especially in the missions, however with the current lull cap and high mob density in these expeditions, it means monks are often resorting to 2 mins down-time FD reset, so bards are the preferred pullers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;C. Decrease in Imitate Death refresh timer&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decrease in ID timer from base 36 minutes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Imitate Death AA has a base refresh timer of 36 minutes, and with Hastened Death this goes down to 24 minutes. As a pulling tool this very long refresh time makes the skill almost useless, and many monks use it purely for the “free” invisibility it gives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The skill needs to have a far faster refresh timer to make it even reasonably useful, say similar to the mend skill (ie, 6 minutes) or even less. Another alternative is to make ID use endurance (similar to bards using mana).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Change the DoDH Hastened Death AA to be a larger decrease than 4 mins per rank. 10 minutes per rank (so down from 6 minutes)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;OR; Add an Extended Hastened Death AA that decreases the ID timer further&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;AA to make ID use END (say, 900 END similar to bards)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;D. Endurance Regenation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Review endurance regeneration rates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Endurance regeneration rates, especially after death is especially slow.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Further AA line for endurance regeneration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fast Endurance regain after death&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Azathool on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;02-11-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;10:27 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
