      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Ok, I will step thru the Top 10 as it applies to me a Non Raiding monk.&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Azathool wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Monks Top 10 List (beta 11 Feb 2006)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;1. Riposte “Immunity”&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Some form of riposte immunity - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;No development feedback at this time&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Monks in a DPS role are generally hitting mobs from behind, however there are times when we are hitting from in front, either by design (mob positioning via Dragon Punch or balancing raid push) or by accident (mob spin). Mobs can do a huge amount of damage on a riposte (1500+ per riposte is common nowadays on trash, and boss mobs riposte for 4k+) This is a lot of “subsidiary” damage we are taking as a DPS class that others whose role is also a DPS class are not as often exposed to (i.e. all DPS casters).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Monks get a lot of strikethrough (via items, and 2 AA lines – Strikethrough and Style of the Mimic), however the mob still gets “an attack” when you “strike through” a riposte, and if it hits you still take damage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Back when mobs only hit for 300 or 400 max, a riposte was of little consequence. Now it’s often the case a double riposte for 4k each can kill a monk.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Given SoE’s oft stated, “damage from any angle” role for monks, it’s currently the case that this is not possible because attacking from the front can result in taking serious damage or even death, and an unwarranted load on healers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An AA line to give a chance of immunity to ripostes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An AA line to tie in Strikethrough to riposte immunity so that if you strike through an opponents attack, you do NOT take riposte damage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These AAs would only work when NOT top of the agro list&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;These AA’s would not work against ENRAGE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fix strikethrough so that you do not get riposted when you strikethrough a riposte&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Not an AA that will ever affect me.. until stike thru is 100% while not at the top of a hate list then DPS will always be better from sides or back. As far as the posistioning aspect, this is almost never the case in a group encounter and only really used on raid bosses to get them set in the right spot and hold them there, still not something that is fight after fight needed.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt; 2. Monk Relative DPS vs other pure melee and other DPS classes&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=""&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Actually get an update on the class re-balancing of DPS (“round 2”) - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;DPS evaluation for all classes has begun and will be the focus of part #2 of the class Re-Envision process&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Monks being one of the three pure DPS classes, [ we feel ] are slightly unbalanced in our relative DPS given like-for-like AA/itemisation against the other melee and “DPS” classes, and the inherent risks we take as a melee class (ie, AoE rampage, ripostes, mobs moving/OOR etc).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’d like to see the results of the DPS re-evaluation “round 2” mentioned many times, and as part of this;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Further evaluation of current monk special attacks&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A new “special” kick style attack&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;I think we should be the best sustained mellee DPS in game, rouges can have burst but on a long fight we should be ahead of them. Our special attacks do not scale with the current game, and the discs we have should last longer than they currently do.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;3. Itemisation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weight of items - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently the biggest issue monks have with itemisation is the weight of items. Many items are far too heavy for monks, even some monk specific items. For example, a full set of DoN cultural with a few bags and average weapons will put a monk overweight. GM symbol augments that weigh 0.5 each again, over 8 slots is far too much. At most they should be 0.1 weight, or even 0 like 90% of all other augments. When items are introduced, we feel it’s very important that when the item is melee orientated it’s weight is carefully considered with the monk weight limit in mind. Items that are “leather class” based again should be considered carefully with monks weight limit in mind, as Druids and Beastlords do not have the same weight limitation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Over expansions we’ve found this is often “forgotten”, with each expansion item weights getting higher and higher, and often each expansion items having to be lowered in weight for the monks via a patch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Not counting the GM armor, most of the groupable upgrades in the last few expansions have been relativly light weight.  rarely see 21 fully equiped, with bags and using Javelins. I agree that devs need to stay vigilant and if GM armor is being used then they should look into making it appropriate weight.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Continuation of the “pouches” introduced with DoDH in future expansions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Careful consideration of the focus effects on future sets of monk armour. The current Anguish items with high Strikethough and zero accuracy is seen by many as asinine.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;A further line of player made throwing items (cf. Javelins), ie, shurikens.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is something I work on every week. I have hunted many many many hours in SF and not seen a starfish, while every caster I know was punching out 15 to 20 runes a session. This is my biggest concern in game. I do apreciate the Runed Javelins, and if I have to spend that much on something I am going to throw away, then thier should be some better Vendor thrown items than those that were created 7 years ago. I have spent many thousands of plat and hours farming for Fishbone darts, Javelins have removed the foraging aspect but still quite a bit to run between abysmal and the bazaar and then log in a chanter to make mana vials. Put some 200 range items on Vendors or increase the drop rate of Starfish.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;More “robe” BP graphics for those who wish to see robes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;More “leather” graphics for those who wish to see the “leather” look - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;4. EMPTY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This item is currently empty (was innate run speed).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;5. Mend Skill&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An AA to reduce the refresh timer on MEND - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Mend has been in the game, unchanged since day one except for the critical mend line that came in when AA’s were first introduced. Whilst a 25% base (50% crit via AA) mend is useful, in today’s game with trash mobs that hit for over 10% of your HP’s PER HIT, we feel it’s time the mend skill got a little additional help beyond the current “critical mend” AA we have.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Add a new AA: Hastened Mend&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;N levels, X percent reduction in timer per level (ie, 5 levels, 6 % per level, down to 4:12 mins )&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Have the tickdown timer on MEND showing how long to refresh once used like other hot keys (ie, Dragon Fang).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;I always looked at mend as emergency use and not something I should be relying on so speeding it up is not that high on my priority. A timer would be nice but I will prolly shoot off a mend @ 0.00 while checking if that happens hehe. (technically - if it can't be used every fight which would just make it hidden HP then there is no real difference between 4 min and 6 min. The only real reason to ask for this is to tank which SoE and 4 other classes don't want us to do anyway and if you try to hide it in being needed to pull continually you would be better off asking earthwalk to be upgraded as long as your not attacking)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;6. EMPTY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This item is currently empty (was Leather graphics, now integrated into item 3)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;7. Disc stacking&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Earthwalk (&amp;amp; Stonestance) should be on it’s own timer (not on the Voiddance/Whirlwind timer) - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Several of the monk disciplines are on the same timer, and in some cases this is overly detrimental, especially when discs now cost END to use so cannot be chained. Using Voiddance (a level 54 disc) currently disables Earthwalk (a 65 disc) for 40 minutes !.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Throw Stone should be on different timer than Lulls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dragon Fang should be on a different timer than Lulls&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;I have always thought all diciplines should be unlinked and we use as our endurance lasts. It will give more emergency type assistance but don't see it really changing how they are used currently.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;8. Weight Limit&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An actual benefit for being under weight - &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently there is no benefit for being “under weight”, only a penalty for being over weight (that being a scaling decrease in the avoidance part of AC as weight goes up.)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The whole concept of a “weight limit” has long been unexplained by SoE given the modern game and modern itemisation, and especially with recent expansions with even some earrings weighing over 1 each, this is often not a limitation, but rather a huge burden.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additionally, the weight limit a long time ago was made to scale with level, starting at a base 14, topping out at &amp;lt; 25 at level 60. However, this cap has not changed with the level 65, and level 70 increases as it should in theory have.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Increase the weight limit cap for level 65 and level 70&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additional Innate increase to runspeed for being underweight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Innate increase in avoidance for bring underweight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Innate increase in attack speed for being underweight&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Have beaten this dead horse enough.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;9. Avoidance&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;An increase to avoidance - &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;Currently being evaluated&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Currently waiting on the outcome of Masters Aura (PoR disc, +5% block/parry/riposte) to see how this affects “avoidance” (via the increase to block and riposte) before expanding on this topic.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;10. EMPTY&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This item is currently empty (was ranged item)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Items that could replace the “empty” slots as follows. I’ve not fully fleshed these out yet as I just wanted to give an idea of some different topic headers that could go in there;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;A. Monk Lull&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Increase the level of mobs that lull affects&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The monk “lull” discs were added with the GoD expansion to give monks more of an even level against other pulling classes. The lulls have scaled up to the OoW expansion so that they cap out at level 70. However with DoDH, many mobs in even mid-difficulty instances are over the level 70 cap, or are totally immune to lull.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Change refresh time on lulls so that more than 1 mob can be lulled&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;I don't think lulls need to be changed till the time comes that devs have upped the non standrd pulling classes lull. When clerics and chanters  get a better lull then I think it will be an issue. As far as multiples that would make pulling so trivial as to not being fun to do anymore. I don't like the crutch to begin with but it is something that was needed when it came out. If your group wants to gamble on losing the cleric or chanter, the 2 main culprits, then thats why they can do multiples, there is a large inherit risk that if it is resisted it's 100% chance they are going to die. So one is fine for us.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B. Pulling Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content that needs pulling&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;One of the primary functions of a monk is pulling. In the OoW expansion this lessened somewhat with open zones, and in DoN disappeared altogether with almost no pulling required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;With DoDH, the pulling role has been somewhat re-established, especially in the missions, however with the current lull cap and high mob density in these expeditions, it means monks are often resorting to 2 mins down-time FD reset, so bards are the preferred pullers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Just keep the content that requires pulling. As long as a puller is needed it won't matter who is preffered puller. There will always be more potential groups than monks and bards combined. Just keep the content challenging.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;C. Decrease in Imitate Death refresh timer&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Decrease in ID timer from base 36 minutes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Imitate Death AA has a base refresh timer of 36 minutes, and with Hastened Death this goes down to 24 minutes. As a pulling tool this very long refresh time makes the skill almost useless, and many monks use it purely for the “free” invisibility it gives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The skill needs to have a far faster refresh timer to make it even reasonably useful, say similar to the mend skill (ie, 6 minutes) or even less. Another alternative is to make ID use endurance (similar to bards using mana).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Change the DoDH Hastened Death AA to be a larger decrease than 4 mins per rank. 10 minutes per rank (so down from 6 minutes)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;OR; Add an Extended Hastened Death AA that decreases the ID timer further&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;AA to make ID use END (say, 900 END similar to bards)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Agree, if this is to be a tool then it needs to be completly re-evaluated. This would close the gap on bards being the &amp;quot;preferred puller&amp;quot;. Even if was usable anytime we would still not be near as effective as a bard with the mez's and snares (and crippling strike is not hardly any use when mobs full health and 2 ticks). As it is, it's a free invis across one zone or one &amp;quot;I ain't waiting 2 min...click every half hour.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;D. Endurance Regenation&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Review endurance regeneration rates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Endurance regeneration rates, especially after death is especially slow.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Further AA line for endurance regeneration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Fast Endurance regain after death&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;It has come full circle, the other night in a wipe on a mission boss it was casters GTG and the mellees doing % call's to FM. There should be some End regen mods/ spells/ disc's somewhere in the game.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Other items.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Still think we should get some kind of Range item to use so I don't have to bandolier between ranged weapons and stat items. Quick fixes still do not address the core issue - every non ranged class gets a free stat placeholder and every other ranged class gets uprgadble ranged items that scale with each expansion. Runed javelins are a bandaid but thats all, I have to make them over and over and over and they still not up to par with most others ranged items.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In general, I like the mission reward upgrades, I like the pulling content in the last couple expansions, so I am mostly happy with the way things are progressing.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;soulfyst&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
