      <description>First, I'll give my response to a couple of the items on the top 10.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Riposte immunity:&lt;br&gt;   I don't currently have any strikethrough AAs or +% from items, but it makes sense to me that if we bypass their defenses to make a hit... that we should BYPASS THEIR DEFENSES when making that hit. Again, I can't bypass a field rat's defenses at this point, but that makes sense to me.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Weight limit:&lt;br&gt;   I'm also frustrated with this. At level 68, I'm still having the same weight issues I had at 60. But at 60, I was in a better position than I was at 50. I would like to see the weight limit scale up with level, or with strength, as I saw suggested on MB. (more on MB after addressing top 10).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Itemization:&lt;br&gt;   As stated by others, this kinda goes hand in hand with weight limit.... but as long as we have a weight limit, this needs to be addressed. Why make a full set of GM armor that causes us to go overweight? That's just silly, and negates the effort involved in getting that armor, whether the effort be from the GM quest itself, or the effort involved in farming enough cash to buy it. I'm not going to turn this into a casual versus raid argument. I'm a casual gamer, small guild, late night player so my grouping is limited to the folks that are online at 3am EST. I understand that this is my choice, as I hate raiding, so I will not begrudge anyone else their ability to more quickly attain money than me.  :)  Long story short, this set takes a good bit of effort to get, and for us non-raiders it is the end-all-be-all of armor for us. But there is a serious penalty for actually wearing it. Wow. That's just messed up.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As far as run speed, I don't feel that needs to be in the list any longer. To answer the potential forthcoming questions, I only have run4. I'm level 68 with 115 AA's, and I'm mostly baz-geared or one-groupable farmed. Guess what? Run speed has been fixed. When one of the best speed buffs available acts as a snare, you really don't need to be running much faster. As for it only being avaliable through AA, I don't seethe problem with that. As has been stated, you can get through your first 50 levels just fine with freebie buffs from non-priest wis casters, if anything at all. I soloed most of my pre-60 career, and did it without many run-speed buffs. After 51, I worked for my first 3 AAs, which incidentally went into runspeed. I got run 4 a while back, and it's more than adequate for the content I'm in. (OoW) Yeah, I want t run faster, but I'll be waiting for the additionals AAs to come in for that. IF it were that big a deal, I suppose I could grind out the AAs over a week. Either way, I will have earned them when the time comes.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To address the eqlive versus Monkly-Business point: What, are you *smurfing* kidding me? Where are you reading this, right now? On SoE's sanctioned board. Grats. Yes, it's aslo been discussed ad nauseum on MB, which I feel is as it should be. You feel that all things monk related should be kept here. I, for one, am glad that it isn't. MB has been separated into multiple forums (Equipment, monk specific quest, newb monk, monk general) that make it much easier to find info that you're looking for, or make suggestions, or to have mildly off-topic, yet still relevant, conversation. There is absolutely nothing wrong with Azathool hosting discussion of the top 10 on MB, as MB is a far busier board than this one. I'm glad that he does. He gets an awful lot of feedback there that allows him to refine his liste BEFORE putting in on the SoE sanctioned board. I guess you should start a crusade to get EQDiva, Steel Warrior, and Samanna all shut down, too.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;God forbid that members of a class should want to gather to duscuss that class in a venue that is less restrictive and better structured to the needs of the class, eh?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I guess that's all for now.  :)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Good list, look forward to seeing where it going int he comming months...years...decades.  :(&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
